Faculty profile




Michael T. GoodrichDistinguished ProfessorDEGREE:Ph.D. 1987, Purdue UniversityRESEARCH AREAS: Algorithms and ComplexityComputer Graphics and VisualizationSecurity and PrivacyRESEARCH INTERESTS: Dr. Goodrich's research is directed at the design of high-performance algorithms and data structures for solving large-scale problems surrounding the increased demands of computer graphics, information visualization, scientific data analysis, information assurance and security, and the Internet. He also is interested in computer science education, specifically ways of more effectively teaching data structures and algorithms.
CONTACT INFORMATION:

E-mail:
goodrich@ics.uci.edu

Office:
DBH 4091

Phone:
